237.3	Roland_Barthes	Roland Barthes	Roland Gérard Barthes (12 November 1915 – 25 March 1980) was a French literary theorist, philosopher, critic, and semiotician. Barthes' ideas explored a diverse range of fields and he influenced the development of schools of theory including structuralism, semiotics, social theory, anthropology and post-structuralism.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/7c/RolandBarthes.jpg/250px-RolandBarthes.jpg
